<title>USA: Sterling Q4 shr loss $0.30 vs loss $0.26.</title>
<headline>Sterling Q4 shr loss $0.30 vs loss $0.26.</headline>
<dateline>EAST MEADOW, N.Y. 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>STERLING VISION, INC. and Subsidiaries</p>
<p>			Consolidated Statement of Operations</p>
<p> For the Three Months Ended December 31   1996	    1995</p>
<p> Systemwide sales (Unaudited)	 $34,778,000   $26,832,000</p>
<p> Revenues				     8,647,000     8,085,000</p>
<p> Loss					 (3,740,000)   (2,643,000)</p>
<p> Loss per share			   (30 cents)     (26 cents)</p>
<p> Shares Outstanding			12,341,000    10,031,000</p>
<p> For the Twelve Months Ended December 31  1996	    1995</p>
<p> Systemwide sales (Unaudited)     $131,593,000   $112,258,000</p>
<p> Revenues				   40,343,000     36,878,000</p>
<p> Net income (loss)		     (4,490,000)	  767,000</p>
<p> Earnings (loss) per share		(36 cts)	    8 cts</p>
<p> Shares Outstanding		     12,341,000     10,031,000</p>
<p>NOTE: For the full year 1996 the company reported a loss of $4,490,000, or $0.36 a share, compared with a profit of $767,000 or $0.08 a share in 1995.</p>
<p>Full name of company is Sterling Vision Inc</p>
